PrecisDesignation of the MINISTER OF INDIAN AND AFFAIRS AND NORTHERN DEVELOPMENT to appoint a senior official representing the Government of Canada as a member of the Implementation Panel, a person to consult and attempt to reach agreement with the Territorial Government and the Designated Inuit Organization on persons to be appointed jointly to the Arbitration Board, and appoint jointly with the Territorial Government and Designated Inuit Organization nine members to the Arbitration Board.
